Daily Operations - Visits and tasks
Overview
- Scope: Ops > Daily Operations (replaces Task Scheduler placeholder).
- Status: Backend Lambdas and frontend dashboard implemented; requires Amplify
  deploy to generate function URLs.

Visit statuses
- SCHEDULED: visit has a scheduled date that is today or in the future (Europe/Madrid).
- OVERDUE: scheduled date is in the past and visit is not terminal.
- COMPLETED / CANCELLED: terminal states (shown together in the Done Kanban column).
- OVERDUE is persisted and recalculated on get/upsert when not terminal.
- Visits cannot be created without a scheduled date.

Task statuses
- UNASSIGNED: no visitId (pool list).
- DISMISS: user dismissed without completing; no visitId; shown in the same pool list.
- PENDING / BLOCKED / COMPLETED: tasks linked to a visit.
- When a visit is cancelled, PENDING/BLOCKED tasks are released to UNASSIGNED.

UI behavior
- Dashboard tab: Kanban with Scheduled | Overdue | Completed & Cancelled.
- Filters: date range (from/to, default today Madrid), quick presets Today and
  Tomorrow, team, status, property, assigned user.
- Visit cards show time, property, visit type, team, assignee, priority, task count,
  hour-bank flag.
- Visit detail modal: edit, complete (requires actual duration hours), cancel,
  tasks list, create task, dismiss task.
- Tasks tab: UNASSIGNED + DISMISS pool; assign to visit, edit, complete, dismiss.
- Assign-to-visit requires matching propertyId and teamId; visit must not be terminal.

Data flow
- DynamoDB tables (existing, not created by Amplify):
  - yalla-visits, yalla-tasks (read/write)
  - yalla-properties, yalla-teams, yalla-users, yalla-visit_types (read-only)
- GSIs used:
  - Visits: scheduledDate-scheduledStartTime-index, propertyId-scheduledDate-index
  - Tasks: visitId-createdAt-index, status-createdAt-index
  - Users: teamId-name-index (when filtering users by team)
- IDs: VISIT-001, TASK-001 sequential format.
- closedBy: Cognito user email on complete actions.

Lambda runtime
- All `defineFunction` handlers use `runtime: 22` (Node.js 22.x on AWS Lambda).
- After changing runtime, redeploy with `npx ampx sandbox` or your pipeline deploy.

Lambdas and endpoints
- GetVisits: query by scheduledDate (single day), scheduledDateFrom +
  scheduledDateTo (max 31 days, one Query per day on GSI), id, or propertyId;
  enriches with taskCountCompleted and taskCountTotal for the visit card badge
  (e.g. 3/5).
- UpsertVisit: create/update visit; cancels release tasks to UNASSIGNED.
- GetTasks: by visitId, id, pool=unassigned, or status.
- UpsertTask: create/update; actions dismiss and assign.
- GetTeams / GetUsers / GetVisitTypes: reference data (active rows).

Frontend endpoint resolution
- VITE_GET_VISITS_URL / custom.getVisitsUrl
- VITE_UPSERT_VISIT_URL / custom.upsertVisitUrl
- VITE_GET_TASKS_URL / custom.getTasksUrl
- VITE_UPSERT_TASK_URL / custom.upsertTaskUrl
- VITE_GET_TEAMS_URL / custom.getTeamsUrl
- VITE_GET_USERS_URL / custom.getUsersUrl
- VITE_GET_VISIT_TYPES_URL / custom.getVisitTypesUrl
- Reuses VITE_GET_PROPERTIES_URL for property selectors.

